#### âœ… Step 1 â€” Install the Blotato Community Node  
- Go to your **n8n Admin Panel**  
- Enable **Verified Community Nodes**  
- Open any workflow and click the â• button to add a node  
- Search for **Blotato**, then click **Install**  

> âš ï¸ If a template shows `???` instead of the Blotato logo:  
Enable Verified Community Nodes **first**, install the Blotato node, and **re-import** the template.

---

#### ğŸ” Step 2 â€” Create Your API Credential  
1. In Blotato, go to **Settings > API**  
2. Click **Generate API Key** and copy it  
3. In n8n, open **Credentials > Blotato API**  
4. Paste your API key, click **Save & Test**, then select this credential on all Blotato nodes  

---

#### ğŸŒ Step 3 â€” Connect Your Social Platforms  
For each **Blotato Publish** node:  
- Select your **Blotato Credential**  
- Choose the platform: TikTok, Instagram, LinkedIn, Facebook, X (Twitter), YouTube Shorts, Threads, Pinterest, or Bluesky  
- For **Pinterest**, you must enter a **Board ID**:  
  - In Blotato, create a sample Pinterest post  
  - Click **Publish**, choose your board  
  - Copy the **Board ID** from the dropdown menu

---

#### ğŸ§ª Step 4 â€” Safe Testing  
When testing:  
- **Deactivate all platform nodes**  
- **Activate only one** (e.g., TikTok)  
- Run the workflow once  
- At the **Upload to Blotato** node, click **Pin Data** to lock the input  
- Then manually **execute** one platform node to verify  
- Once confirmed, activate the others and continue testing  

---

#### ğŸ“Š Step 5 â€” Monitor Requests in Blotato  
Use the [**Blotato API Dashboard**](https://my.blotato.com/api-dashboard) to:  
- Review each request  
- Inspect payloads  
- Check error messages if something goes wrong
